snippet.textDisplay: Having driven all 3 (lesser trim levels obviously), I'd take the Challenger for a street driven car, then Mustang, then Camaro. The Challenger is the heavyweight but it's also the most comfortable. Has the most interior space (when you're tall that's important) and best visibility. The Mustang is middle of the road, and the Camaro feels the most cramped and visibility is pretty bad, when you're tall and look to the side, you see the ceiling, have to bend down to see out the window.
snippet.textOriginal: Having driven all 3 (lesser trim levels obviously), I'd take the Challenger for a street driven car, then Mustang, then Camaro.
